	'description' => Tie::IxHash->new(
		'introduction' 		   			=> "Backup and protect the data on your Linux machines using the scripts bundle provided by $AppConfig::appType. Protect files during transfer and storage, using 256-bit AES encryption with an optional private key.",
		'system_requirements'  			=> "Linux (CentOS/Ubuntu/Fedora/OpenSUSE/FreeBSD/Linux Mint/Raspberry Pi) - 32-bit/64-bit\nPerl v5.8 or later",
		'setup_account' 	   			=> "You need to have an $AppConfig::appType account to use the scripts bundle for performing backup of your files. In case you do not have an account, sign up and create an account at \n$AppConfig::accountSignupURL\n\nTo set up the $AppConfig::appType scripts bundle locally with your $AppConfig::appType account, run the below command and follow the instructions.\n\n\$./account_setting.pl\n\nYou may be prompted to install the required Linux packages on your Operating System. In order to deliver faster sync, backup and continuous data protection, some of these packages are required.\n\nNote: On setting up the script bundle for the first time, users will be asked to enter the service path. This path will contain user specific data required to perform operations via script bundle.",
		'setup_account_IDrive' 			=> "\nYou can authenticate with $AppConfig::appType credentials or SSO credentials. \n\nNote: Single Sign-On (SSO) allows users to login to multiple systems with just one set of credentials. Now $AppConfig::appType Linux scripts  is SSO enabled, users can use their SSO credentials to login to the $AppConfig::appType Linux scripts.\n\nNote: The two-factor authentication provides additional security to your account and helps in preventing unauthorized access. Once two-factor authentication is enabled via web, in addition to your password, you will need to enter a verification code sent to your email address or phone number or Time-based OTP authenticator app, while signing in to your $AppConfig::appType account.\n\nNote: For some $AppConfig::appType accounts, while configuring the account, 'Create New Backup Location'/'Select from existing Backup Locations' option will appear and 'Mirror'/'Relative' backup type option will not appear.",
		'login_account' 	   			=> "If you are not logged in to your $AppConfig::appType account while setting up your bundle, run the below command to login:\n\n\$./login.pl\n\nNote: Login script is a mandatory script to be executed before performing any operation. This script will authenticate your $AppConfig::appType account details and will create a secure session for your backups.\n\nYou can login with $AppConfig::appType credentials or SSO credentials. \n\nNote: Single Sign-On (SSO) allows users to login to multiple systems with just one set of credentials. Now $AppConfig::appType Linux scripts  is SSO enabled, users can use their SSO credentials to login to the $AppConfig::appType Linux scripts.\n\nNote: The two-factor authentication provides additional security to your account and helps in preventing unauthorized access. Once two-factor authentication is enabled via web, in addition to your password, you will need to enter a verification code sent to your email address or phone number or Time-based OTP authenticator app, while signing in to your $AppConfig::appType account.",
		'2fa' 							=> "The two-factor authentication provides additional security to your account and helps in preventing unauthorized access. Once two-factor authentication is enabled via web, in addition to your password, you will need to enter a verification code sent to your email address or phone number or generated via Time-based OTP authenticator app, while signing in to your $AppConfig::appType Backup account.\n\n\nTo sign in after two-factor authentication is enabled,\n\n1. If you have selected Email address or Phone number as the preferred method of receiving one-time verification code, enter the same.\nNote: You can also add your computer as a trusted device by selecting the Trust this computer. Once a computer is added as a trusted device, users will not be asked to enter verification code during any subsequent sign in.\n\n2. If you have selected Time-based OTP authentication as the preferred method of receiving one-time verification code, enter the one-time code generated by the Time-based OTP authenticator app in your mobile device.",
		#'edit_supported_files'  		=> "The user must provide the file or folder list required to backup/local backup/restore in the backup/local backup/restore set file respectively, before starting the operation.\nTo update these details in the backup/local backup/restore set file execute the below command:\n\n\$./edit_supported_files.pl\n\nThe menu option will be displayed.\nSelect option 1 to modify the backup set.\nOnce the respective file opens in the text editor you can add the files/folders for backup.\nUsing the same script you can update, exclude and even schedule backup/local backup/restore set file by selecting the desired option.",
		'edit_backupset_file'  		 	=> "Before starting the backup operation, you must add the list of files/folders required for the backup in the backup set file. To update these details in the backup set file, you must execute the below command:\n\n\$./edit_supported_files.pl\n\nSelect option \"Edit your Backupset\" in the menu option appeared, to edit the backup set file. The respective file will open in the selected editor to edit. Add the files/folders that need to be backed up.",
		'edit_local_backupset_file'	    => "Before starting local backup operation, you must add the list of files/folders required for local backup in the local backup set file.\n\nTo update these details in the local backup set file, you must execute the below command:\n\n\$./edit_supported_files.pl\n\nSelect option \"Edit your Local Backupset\" in the menu option appeared, to edit the local backup set file. The respective file will open in the selected editor to edit. Add the files/folders that need to be backed up.",
		'edit_restoreset_file'  		=> "Before starting the restore operation, you must add the list of files/folders required for restore in the restore set file.\n\nTo update these details in the restore set file, execute the below command:\n\n\$./edit_supported_files.pl\n\nSelect option \"Edit your Restoreset\" in the menu option appeared, to edit the restore set file. The respective file will open in the selected editor to edit. Add the files/folders that need to be restored.",
        'edit_local_restoreset_file'	=> "Before starting the local restore operation, you must add the list of files/folders required to restore in the local restore set file.\n\nTo update these details in the local restore set file, you must execute the below command:\n\n\$./edit_supported_files.pl\n\nSelect option \"Edit your Local Restoreset\" in the menu option appeared, to edit the local restore set file. The respective file will open in the editor. Add the files/folders that need to be restored.",
		'manual_backup' 				=> "You can perform immediate/manual backup using the below command:\n\n\$./Backup_Script.pl\n\nWhen you run your backup script, it will reconfirm your backup location and allow you to change it. You can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting backed up. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.\n\nIf you want your script to not ask for a backup location and or display progress bars, then you can always use the \"--silent\" flag with this command.",
		'manual_backup_IDrive' 			=> "\nNote: For some IDrive accounts, this script will not provide an option to change 'Backup location'.",
		'manual_local_backup' 		    => "You can perform immediate/manual local backup using the below command:\n\n\$./local_backup.pl\n\nUsing this script, you can backup your Linux machine data to the express device shipped to you. You can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting backed up. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.\n\nOnce the data is backed up, you can ship this express device back to us and within a week your data will be available in your $AppConfig::appType account.\nFor more details on express, visit $expressBackupPage",
		'manual_restore' 				=> "You can perform immediate/manual restore using the below command:\n\n\$./Restore_Script.pl\n\nWhen you run your restore script, it will reconfirm your 'to' and 'from' restore location and will allow you to change it, if required. You can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting restored. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.\n\nIf you want your script to not ask for the ‘to’ and ‘from’ restore location, or to display the progress bars, then you can always use the \"--silent\" flag with this command.",
		'manual_local_restore' 		    => "You can perform immediate/manual local restore using the below command:\n\n\$./local_restore.pl\n\nUsing this script, you can safely retrieve all your locally backed up files/folders to your Linux machine. You can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting restored. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.\n\n",
		'manual_restore_IDrive' 		=> "\nNote: For some $AppConfig::appType accounts, user will not be able to edit \"Restore From\" manually and have to select \"Restore From\" location from the list of existing locations.",
		#'schedule_backup' 				=> "Run the below command to manage your schedule backup/local backup/archive cleanup job:\n\n\$./scheduler.pl\n\nSelect the desired menu option to  create, edit, view or delete your schedule backup / local backup / archive cleanup job and follow the instructions.\nIn case you want your schedule job to stop automatically at a scheduled time then you can set a cut-off time as well.",
		'schedule_online_backup'		=> "Run the below command & follow the instructions to manage your schedule backup job:\n\n\$./scheduler.pl\n\nSchedule your backup job:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Schedule your backup job\" menu option to create/edit your schedule and follow the instructions. In case you want your scheduled job to stop automatically at a scheduled time, then set the cut-off time, while following the instructions.\n\nDisable scheduled backup job:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Disable scheduled backup job\" menu option to disable your scheduled backup job.",
		'schedule_local_backup'		    => "Run the below command & follow the instructions to manage your schedule local backup job:\n\n\$./scheduler.pl\n\nSchedule your local backup job:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Schedule your local backup job\" menu option to create/edit the schedule and follow the instructions.\n$AppConfig::tab In case you want your scheduled job to stop automatically at a scheduled time, then set the cut-off time, while following the instructions.\n\nDisable scheduled local backup job:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Disable scheduled local backup job\" menu option to disable your scheduled local backup job.",
		'archive_cleanup'				=> "Archive Cleanup compares the files of your local storage, selected for backup, with the files in your $AppConfig::appType online backup account. It then deletes the files present in your account but not on your local machine. This feature thus helps you to free up space in your online backup account.\n\nWhen you run the script to perform archive cleanup, you can enter a percentage of the total number of files to be considered for deletion. This percentage based control helps to avoid large-scale deletion of files from your account.\n\n",
		'archive_cleanup_IBackup'		=> "\nNote:\n1. For your $AppConfig::appType account if \"relative path\" option is enabled then user will not able to perform Archive cleanup operation.\n2. Manual/periodic Cleanup cannot be initiated when backup is in progress.",
		'archive_cleanup_IDrive'		=> "\nNote:\n1. For some $AppConfig::appType accounts \"relative path\" option will be available. If \"relative path\" is enabled, then the user will not able to perform the Archive Cleanup operation.\n2. Manual/Periodic Cleanup cannot be initiated when backup is in progress.",
		'periodic_archive'				=> "Periodic Cleanup deletes files at the frequency & percentage set by you for the current backup set, once enabled.\n\nRun the below command & follow the instructions to manage your periodic archive cleanup job:\n\n\$./scheduler.pl\n\nPeriodic Archive Cleanup:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Periodic Archive Cleanup\" menu option to create/edit the schedule and follow the instructions.\n\nDisable Periodic Archive Cleanup:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Disable Periodic Archive Cleanup\" menu option to disable your periodic archive cleanup job.",
		'manual_archive' 				=> "To perform archive cleanup operation, run the below command and follow the instructions:\n\n\$./archive_cleanup.pl\n\nWhen you run the script to perform archive cleanup, you can modify the percentage of the total no.of files to be considered for deletion.\nThis percentage based control helps you to avoid large-scale deletion of files from your account.",
		'version_restore' 				=> "You can view the list of previous versions of any file and select any version that you want to restore.\n\nTo retrieve a file with earlier versions, run the below command and follow the instructions:\n\n\$./restore_version.pl",
		'version_restore_IDrive' 		=> "\nNote: For some IDrive accounts, user will not be able to edit \"Restore From\" location manually and have to select \"Restore From\" location from the list of existing locations.",
		'snapshots' 					=> "Snapshots are historical view of your data, stored in $AppConfig::appType account, which allow you to perform point-in-time recovery. They are useful especially in case your systems were attacked by ransomware or other malicious software.\n\nIf your data is infected with encryption-based ransomware, all you need to do is select a time-line before the infection and restore it. As $AppConfig::appType is cross-platform compatible you can ensure all your PCs and Macs are backed up and protected against these threats.\n\nThe additional storage requirements for Snapshots has no impact on your $AppConfig::appType account storage space.",
		'snapshots_IDrive' 			    => "\nNote: For some accounts, Snapshots are not available.",
		#'view_progress' 				=> "To view the progress of scheduled backup or local backup operation, run the below command:\n\n\$./Status_Retrieval_Script.pl",
		'view_backup_progress' 	 		=> "To view the progress of backup, run the below command and select \"Backup Job\" menu option:\n\n\$./status_retrieval.pl\n\nYou can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting backed up. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.",
		'view_local_backup_progress'	=> "To view the progress of ongoing local backup, run the below command and select \"Local Backup Job\" menu option:\n\n\$./status_retrieval.pl\n\nYou can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting backed up. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.",
		'view_restore_progress'			=> "To view the progress of ongoing restore job, run the below command and select \"Restore Job\" menu option:\n\n\$./status_retrieval.pl\n\nYou can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting restored. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.",
		'view_local_restore_progress'	=> "To view the progress of ongoing local restore, run the below command and select \"Local Restore Job\" menu option:\n\n\$./status_retrieval.pl\n\nYou can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting restored. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'.",
		#'stop_ongoing_operations' 		=> "To stop an ongoing backup or local backup or restore operation, run the below command:\n\n\$./job_termination.pl",
		'stop_online_backup' 			=> "To stop an ongoing backup job, run the below command and select \"Stop Backup\" menu option:\n\n\$./job_termination.pl",
		'stop_local_backup' 			=> "To stop an ongoing local backup job, run the below command and select \"Stop Local Backup\" menu option:\n\n\$./job_termination.pl",
		'stop_online_restore' 			=> "To stop an ongoing restore job, run the below command and select \"Stop Restore\" menu option:\n\n\$./job_termination.pl",
		'stop_local_restore' 			=> "To stop an ongoing local restore job, run the below command and select \"Stop Local Restore\" menu option:\n\n\$./job_termination.pl",
		'logs' 			 		        => "You can view or delete the logs for backup/local backup/continuous data protection/restore/archive cleanup operations using the below command:\n\n\$./logs.pl",
		'send_error_report' 			=> "You can send error report to $AppConfig::appType support by running the below command:\n\n\$./send_error_report.pl",
		'edit_user_details' 			=> "In case you want to reconfigure your IDrive account locally due to any reason or want to edit user details locally for your configured IDrive account, run the below command:\n\n\$./account_setting.pl\n\nOnly if your account is already configured in the current machine, you will find the menu which will allow you to reconfigure your IDrive account locally or will allow you to edit the user account details locally.\n\nYou can configure the following settings:\n\n",
		'logout_account' 				=> "To end the logged in session for your $AppConfig::appType account, run the below command:\n\n\$./logout.pl\n\nYou must logout (optional) to avoid any unauthorized access to your $AppConfig::appType account. After logout, you need to login again to perform most of the operations.\nNote: Your scheduled backup/scheduled local backup/continuous data protection/periodic cleanup jobs will run even after you log out.",
		'updating_script_bundle' 		=> "Every script that gets executed, displays a header which provides the details of the logged in $AppConfig::appType account. Same header also displays information on any newly available script bundle.\n\nIf Software Update Notification is enabled, you will see the message \"A new update is available. Run check_for_update.pl to update to the latest package\", indicating that a new improved version of the script bundle has been released.\n\nTo update to the most recent available script bundle, run the below command and follow the instructions:\n\n\$./check_for_update.pl",
		'uninstall_script_bundle' 		=> "Uninstalling the script bundle from your system will leave the files/folders of your system liable to digital disasters.\n\nTo uninstall the script bundle, run the below command and follow the instructions.\n\n\$./Uninstall_Script.pl\nThis script will automatically remove all $AppConfig::appType package files and other dependency files. It will also stop all $AppConfig::appType specific services and cleanup the scheduled backup/local backup/continuous data protection/periodic cleanup jobs, if any.",

		#Sub-Title script  files/folder
		#'script_download_executable_files' => "1.account_setting.pl\n2.archive_cleanup.pl\n3.Backup_Script.pl\n4.check_for_update.pl\n5.edit_supported_files.pl\n6.local_backup.pl\n7.job_termination.pl\n8.login.pl\n9.logout.pl\n10.Restore_Script.pl\n11.restore_version.pl\n12.scheduler.pl\n13.send_error_report.pl\n14.speed_analysis.pl\n15.Status_Retrieval_Script.pl\n16.Uninstall_Script.pl\n17.view_log.pl\n",
		#'script_download_supported_files'  => "1.Constants.pm\n2.cron.pl\n3.Header.pl\n4.Operations.pl\n5.readme.txt\n6.utility.pl\n",
		#'script_download_supported_folders' => "Ibackuplib - Contains cron startup routine files for all supported platforms and required Perl modules",

		#Sub-Title Exclude
		'exclude_files_full_Path'    => "To exclude files/folders with full path,\n\n1. Run 'edit_supported_files.pl' script and select option 'Edit Your Full Path Exclude List'. The 'FullExcludeList.txt' file will open in the selected editor.\n2. Add the full path of the files/folders that you wish to exclude.\n3. Enter each item in a new line.\n4. Save and exit.\n\nExample: Your backup set contains \"/home/Documents\" and if you want to exclude \"/home/Documents/temp\", enter the folder path ie: \"/home/Documents/temp\" in FullExcludeList file.",
		'exclude_files_partial_Path' => "To exclude files/folders with partial path,\n\n1. Run 'edit_supported_files.pl' script and select option 'Edit Your Partial Path Exclude List'. The 'PartialExcludeList.txt' file will open in the selected editor.\n2. Add the partial name of the files/folders that you wish to exclude.\n3. Enter each item in a new line.\n4. Save and exit.\n\nExample: Your backup set contains /home/Documents and if you want to exclude all the pst files from this folder like\n/home/Documents/design tutorials.pst,\n/home/Documents/new.pst,\n/home/Documents/James/tutorials.pst etc, then enter 'pst' in PartialExcludeList file.",
		'exclude_files_regex'        => "To exclude files/folders based on regex pattern,\n\n1. Run 'edit_supported_files.pl' script and select option 'Edit Your Regex Exclude List'. The 'RegexExcludeList.txt' file will open in the selected editor.\n2. Add the regex pattern of the files/folders that you wish to exclude.\n3. Enter each item in a new line.\n4. Save and exit.\n\nExample: Your backup set contains /home/Folder01, /home/Folder02, /home/FolderA, /home/FolderB.\nIf you want to exclude all folders/files that contain numeric values in name ie: /home/Folder01, /home/Folder02 etc, then enter 'Folder\\d+' in the RegexExcludeList file.",

		#Sub-Title Edit user details
		'edit_user_details_backup_setting'   		=> "Backup location:\n$AppConfig::tab Update the backup location using this option.\n\nBackup type:\n$AppConfig::tab Change the backup type from mirror to relative and vice versa using this option.\n\nBackupset Rescan Interval:\n$AppConfig::tab Set the interval in which IDrive service scans through the backup set and keeps the list of files to backup updated.\n\nBandwidth throttle(%):\n$AppConfig::tab Set the Internet bandwidth to be used by the scripts for backups using this option.\n\nFailed files(%):\n$AppConfig::tab By default, failed files % to notify backup as 'Failure' is set to 5%. If the total files failed for backup is more than 5%, then backup will be notified as failure. Change the default setting using this option.\n\nIgnore file/folder level permission error:\n$AppConfig::tab If your backup set contains files/folders that have insufficient access rights, IDrive will not be able to backup those files/folders. Hence in such a case, by default, your backup will be considered as 'Failure'. To ignore file/folder level access rights/permission errors, enable this setting.\n\nMissing files(%):\n$AppConfig::tab By default, missing files % to notify backup as 'Failure' is set to 5%. If the total files missing for backup is more than 5%, then backup will be notified as failure. Change the default setting using this option.\n\nShow hidden files/folders:\n$AppConfig::tab Disable this option to skip hidden files/folders from backup.\n\nUpload multiple file chunks simultaneously:\n$AppConfig::tab Enable this option to upload multiple file chunks simultaneously to improve overall data transfer speed.",
		'edit_user_details_backup_setting_IDrive'   => "\nNote: For some users, while reconfiguring or editing account, \"Backup Type\" will not be displayed.",
		'edit_user_details_general_setting'  		=> "Desktop access:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to enable/disable the dashboard access. For some IDrive accounts, this option will not be available.\n\nE-mail address:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to change the email address provided at the time of setting up an account locally.\n\nProxy details:\n$AppConfig::tab If you are behind a proxy address, you should update the proxy settings using this option.\n\nService path:\n$AppConfig::tab Update the service path used by IDrive scripts using this option.\n\nSoftware update notification:\n$AppConfig::tab Enable this option to get a notification for available updates in the script header.",
		'edit_user_details_restore_setting'  		=> "Restore from location:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to change the location from where items will be restored.\n\nRestore location:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to change the restore location.\n\nRestore location prompt:\n$AppConfig::tab Enable this option if you wish to receive notification about the restore location before starting restore.",
		'edit_user_details_restore_setting_IDrive'  => "\nNote: For some users, while editing \"Restore From\" location, list of devices will appear.",
		'edit_user_details_services'       	 		=> "Start/Restart CDP service:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to start or restart the CDP service. This service is responsible for identifying any change that takes place in your local storage for the selected backup set items and pushing that change for backup via CDP (if enabled) or via scheduled backup operation.\n\nStart/Restart dashboard service:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to start or restart dashboard service. This service must be up and running for your machine to be remotely managed from the Linux web interface (Dashboard).\n\nStart/Restart $AppConfig::appType Cron service:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to start or restart $AppConfig::appType Cron service. This service is responsible for all the scheduled jobs to work as expected.",
		# 'edit_user_details_services_IDrive'  		=> "\nStart/Restart Dashboard service:\n$AppConfig::tab Use this option to start/restart the dashboard service. This service must be up and running for your machine to be remotely managed from the Dashboard.",
		'what_is_cdp'			=> "Continuous Data Protection feature automatically recognizes the changes made to the files (limited to 5 GB in size) in the backup set and starts the backup operation in near real-time. CDP is not a replacement for the traditional schedule backup feature but works along with scheduled backup to provide timely protection to your data.",
		'schedule_cdp'			=> "Run the below command & follow the instructions to manage your scheduled CDP job:\n\n\$./scheduler.pl\n\nSchedule your CDP Job:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Schedule your CDP Job\" menu option to create/edit your schedule and follow the instructions.\n\nDisable scheduled CDP job:\n$AppConfig::tab Select the \"Disable Scheduled CDP Job\" menu option to disable your scheduled CDP job.",
		'view_cdp_progress'		=> "To view the progress of ongoing CDP, run the below command and select \"CDP Job\" menu option:\n\n\$./status_retrieval.pl\n\nYou can view the graphical progress bar for viewing the progress details of your data getting backed up. If you want to view the detailed progress bar, press '+' and to collapse, press '-'",
		'stop_cdp'				=> "To stop an ongoing CDP job, run the below command and select \"Stop CDP Job\" menu option:\n\n\$./job_termination.pl",
	),
);
